  "prompt": "Is it unsafe to eat shrimp or fish that has been left out on the counter overnight then refrigerated? Twice?",
  "response": "Yes, it is unsafe to eat shrimp or fish that has been left out at room temperature for an extended period, such as overnight. Bacteria can multiply rapidly in perishable foods like seafood when they are not kept at safe temperatures. The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) recommends that seafood should not be left out for more than two hours at room temperature; if the temperature is above 90\u00b0F (32\u00b0C), that time is reduced to just one hour.\n\nRefrigerating the seafood after it has been left out does not make it safe to eat, as harmful bacteria may have already formed. Cooking the seafood may kill some bacteria, but it won't eliminate any toxins that could have been produced by bacteria during the time it was left out. For food safety, it is best to discard shrimp or fish that has been improperly stored.",
